<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Start Menu v4.0.4 - v4.1.0 Comparisons Available]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2619&amp;p=12751#p12751"><![CDATA[
Yes downloading the installer by visiting <!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net">www.classicshell.net</a><!-- w --> and starting it by double clicking it is called a manual upgrade. An automatic upgrade is when Classic Shell's Update component automatically checks for an update and notifies you and if you choose to upgrade, then it will automatically download the installer for you and copy it to your Downloads folder. After that, you must still double click the installer to start the upgrade process.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Fri May 09, 2014 6:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
